I just got into EQ at the start of this summer but I’ve found although it’s nice to get nice gear at the end of a day of long waiting and sitting its still not all that much fun doing it.  Fighting the same mobs over and over and this is just with my guild… trying to find a group by myself although many tell me that I’m one of the better druids they’ve met is still a pain in the ass.  <br>
<br>
Which leads me to another point why is it that everyone says druids are the best soloers?  Have they not noticed that other classes namely any pure casters can out nuke us and give themselves mana regen… necros, shammys, bards, enchanters.  Hell even clerics can out nuke us I’m not asking to be able to nuke like a wizzy or anything but I really do think we need something later on in the game.  Or perhaps the reason we are verrants red headed step chilled is because there’s so many of us.  But this only proves how uncustomizable this game is.<br>
<br>
There was a lot of things in EQ that where great, like the whole social setup with the thousands of people online at any given time.  Also the exploration of new lands was really cool but this didn’t make up for the over all repetitiveness that is Everquest.  <br>
<br>
Perhaps I’ll get flamed for this even though its like apples and oranges… a game like say Diablo 2 or a FPS is actually fun to pickup and just play… where as EQ with all of the bothers like character selection and camping to quit you waste have your time doing crap and then once you get in you just hit auto attack and… I hit you for 4 damage… maybe I’m just a young kid who never played dungeons and dragons but I f*cking loath this whole setup.  I don’t know why they had to stay based with the old regulations when they could have made it a bit more fresh and exciting.<br>
<br>
The only thing that kept me going in EQ was the promise of being a tough ass player but with the amount of mundane crap out there it just doesn’t seem worth it.<br>
<br>
Not to mention the fact that you have to pay $15 a month so you can't exactly can your account and then just pick the game back up later.  <br>
<br>
I really feel attached to my characters but I just feel its no longer productive to waste my time.<br>
